# Tasks archive — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Completed tasks, moved here the moment a task reaches `done` (by the `commit` skill, not at session close). Same entry format as `TASKS.md`, plus a `done:` date — this is a historical record, not a place to edit.

Always check this file first when looking for a recently completed task — it's the current, most-recent archive. Once it reaches 50 entries, it gets split: moved into `tasks-archive/TASKS_ARCHIVE_{start-date}_{end-date}.md` (covering the `done:` date range of the entries it holds at that point, creating the `tasks-archive/` folder the first time this happens), logged as a row in `TASKS_ARCHIVE_INDEX.md`, and a fresh empty `TASKS_ARCHIVE.md` takes over collecting new completions at the project root. Splits live in their own folder rather than the project root so a project with years of history doesn't end up with a dozen loose dated files cluttering the top-level directory listing. Only dig into `TASKS_ARCHIVE_INDEX.md` — and whichever file under `tasks-archive/` it points to — if what you need isn't in this current file.

